&lt;p&gt;Our main tech stack includes:&lt;br&gt;- AWS for all of our Infrastructure&lt;br&gt;- Docker&lt;br&gt;- Python (Django, Flask)&lt;br&gt;- MySQL&lt;br&gt;- MongoDB&lt;br&gt;- Redis&lt;br&gt;We use also:&lt;br&gt;- PostgreSQL&lt;br&gt;- Node.js&lt;br&gt;- Java&lt;br&gt;- BigQuery&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;‚óè Support, coach, and develop team members into top-performing engineers.&lt;br&gt;‚óè Working closely in cross-functional teams where everyone is responsible for the outcome.&lt;br&gt;‚óè Build a great place to work for talented and motivated people&lt;br&gt;‚óè Designing, developing, and deploying backend services focusing on high availability, fault&amp;nbsp;tolerance, low latency, and security.&lt;br&gt;‚óè Take full end-to-end responsibility for the services your team owns, from development to&amp;nbsp;production, operations, and data.&lt;br&gt;‚óè Develop innovative solutions with Bitcoin at its core.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills needed:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;‚óè Significant software engineering experience in one or more general-purpose programming&amp;nbsp;languages (we use Python and Node.js)&lt;br&gt;‚óè Excellent teamwork and communication skills, comfortable preparing high-quality&amp;nbsp;documentation and designs to aid understanding and knowledge sharing.&lt;br&gt;‚óè Understanding the microservices architecture, container-based 12-factor apps, and&amp;nbsp;cloud-native patterns around fault tolerance.&lt;br&gt;‚óè Track record of using Event Storming and Domain Driven Design, delivering highly scalable&amp;nbsp;asynchronous software.&lt;br&gt;‚óè Experience building contract-first services and adopting patterns and frameworks to enable&amp;nbsp;appropriate automated testing at the unit, contract, service, and end-to-end levels.&lt;br&gt;‚óè Experience building services that can be deployed on demand, quickly, and with quality.&lt;br&gt;‚óè Excellent understanding of CI/CD patterns and good practice.&lt;br&gt;‚óè Understand the role of high-quality observability in building highly scalable and performant&amp;nbsp;software.&lt;/p&gt;
